title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, April 9, 1872
object_transcript: Shopiere Apr. 9th '72, Friend Etta, I have been waiting impatiently for the time to come when I should be well enough to answer your letter. Mother made me go to bed the day after I came home and I stayed there for a long time it seems to me. ...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, December 3, 1873
object_transcript: Bradford, Dec. 3rd 1873, Friend, I dare say eer this the news of my flight eastward has reached your careless ear. Well: I have taught three days like my school very much & could not ask for a nicer class. My large boys are three which numbers is to be increased by two when the term of school at Clinton closes. ...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, September 16, 1874
object_transcript: Bradford, Wisc., 1 Sept. 16th 74, Friend Ettie, Although you dont deserve one mite of my attention. Hurrah for a chat!!, I am at the church as usual with only three scholars though today I’ve sent two of them for water & set the other playing hide & seek or snap & catch with her shadow around the stove. ...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, February 22, 1875
object_transcript: Feb 22nd 1875, Dear Ettie, I begin to think it is about time to answer your letter, I am quite well but feeling very tired just now for I have been up for the last two or three evenings there is a great deal of sickness around & you know I can never refuse to do any thing that I can do. ...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, March 14, 1875
object_transcript: Janesville Wisconsin, March 14th. 1875, Dear Ettie: I have neglected you, am sorry consequently command you to forgive me. I am home as you will see by this letter came last Thursday and you may sin again I scolded some when you went home without coming to see me once. ...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, September 8, 1876
object_transcript: Bennett Valley Cal., Sept. 8, 1876, Dear True Friend Ettie,, Perhaps you know how glad I was to get your letter; but I scarcely think you do indeed words fail me when I would portran [portray] to you my great joy. for believe me I had not a word from this. until your epistle was handed me. except a few words in John’s letter from Libbie...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, May 3, 1879
object_transcript: Black’s School District, Trout Brook Ranche May 3 '79, Dear Friend Ettie, Again my silence is broken why is it that we keep up such a thinking without allowing one thought expression. I have been very busy of late, in school, very pleasantly situated good salary with the prospect of an increase in wages next year ...

title: Emma J. Thayer letter to Juliette A. E. Flagler, September 20, 1874
object_transcript: Bradford, Wisc., Sept. 20, 74, Dear Friend Ettie, Your welcome epistle was recd. last evening. It was a real surprise to me for I had not thought that you would answer for several weeks. I knew you would have a great deal to do with what little strength you had ...
